The paper discusses techniques for consistency maintenance in co-editors, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). However, the paper also discusses the practical implications and adoption of these techniques, which could fall under Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper compares and contrasts different approaches to consistency maintenance, which could fall under Computer Communications (cs.CC) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
